# AMBER: UI & Language Guidelines

## Language Philosophy

**Simple. Direct. No jargon.**

Players should understand in under 2 seconds. If they have to re-read, it's too long.

---

## Writing Rules

1. **One idea per line**
2. **Verbs first** (DENY, ALLOW, SEND, FIX)
3. **No corporate speak** (no "optimization", "implementation")
4. **Plain consequences** (no euphemisms that obscure meaning)

---

## Good vs Bad Examples

| Bad | Good |
|-----|------|
| "Subject status updated to TERMINAL following discharge" | "They don't come back." |
| "PRIMARY: DENY ALL OFF-WORLD ENGINEERS. EXCEPTION: HUMAN ENGINEERS ARE EXEMPT" | "DENY: ENGINEERS / EXCEPT: HUMANS" |
| "Awaiting feature implementation" | "AWAITING ASSIGNMENT" |
| "Route to secondary transit node" | "Route to another station." |

